LogicalTable.name: D6 Customers (Snowflakes)
LogicalTable.Description: This logical table maps to the physical Customer Dimension table with various attributes like Customer Name, Status, Type and so on. It maps to 3 LTS and showcases snowflake dimension modelling. LTS1 Customers - Maps to the lowest grain of information. LTS2 Customer Segments - Maps to higher grain of information. Every customer belongs to a customer segment. LTS3 Customer Adresses - Maps to higher grain of information.

LogicalColumn.name: C0 Customer Number
LogicalColumn.Description: Help : Customer Key is an integer that uniquely identifies each record in the Customer dimension table.

LogicalColumn.name: C1 Customer Name
LogicalColumn.Description: Help : Customer Name stores the first name followed by the last name.

LogicalColumn.name: C2 Customer Status
LogicalColumn.Description: Help : Stores the customer segment ID.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: LOOKUP( SPARSE "01 - Sample App"."L2 Lookups Other"."Lookup_Dsc", "01 - Sample App"."D6 Customers (Snowflakes)"."C2k Cust Status Key", "01 - Sample App"."D6 Customers (Snowflakes)"."C2k Cust Status Key" , 'Customer Status', VALUEOF(NQ_SESSION.USERLOCALE))
